    "faq_section_dyFFbm": {
      "type": "faq-section",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_hJ3tiH": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Why are lab grown diamonds trending now?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Value driven luxury is demanded by modern couples and rightly so. They offer the same sparkle and durability as natural diamonds, while significantly driving down costs. These are not conflict diamonds, and their origin can be traced making them the smarter and more conscious choice taken by young buyers. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_DRgEDg": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the future of lab grown diamonds?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>The future of lab grown diamonds is strong and rapidly rising. With carefully crafted bespoke pieces in varied colored diamonds, lab grown diamond jewelry are trendsetters every coming year.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_9WUayJ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How are lab grown diamonds better for the environment?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Lab grown diamonds are better for the environment in multiple ways - no soil erosion and land disruption, no pollution caused due to mining, and avoid high carbon emissions and excessive water usage. They are not conflict diamonds, making them a more ethical choice. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_nfwCGw": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Can a lab grown diamond cut glass?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>There are two main types of lab grown diamonds: CVD (Chemical Vapr Deposition and HPHT (High Pressure High Temperature), both of which are methods of growing diamonds in simulated environments. CVD uses carbon rich gas to grow diamond layers, while HPHT mimics the natural way of growing diamonds by creating a similar environment of intense heat and pressure. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_Peiixq": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What machine is used to grow lab-grown diamonds?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Lab grown diamonds are created using highly specialized machines such as the CVD reactor and HPHT press. A CVD reactor is a vacuum chamber that uses gas and plasma to grow diamond crystals layer by layer, while a HPHT press helps create an environment similar to the natural one to create diamonds under intense heat and pressure. Both these machines help create man made diamonds with more control allowing diamonds to grow with precision and purity without harming the environment.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
